    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-15T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-15T06:00:00-05:00" n="365"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d365">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50 Recovery/10–1548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Political Adviser</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Joyce</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Trieste, to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Trieste</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-15T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 15, 1948—noon.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_niact1">Niact</gloss> 679. Remytel 673 of October 14.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d365fn1">Not printed.</note> General Airey and I at 9 o’clock
                    this morning, Trieste time, signed bilateral agreement covering participation
                    British/US zone <gloss target="#t_FTT1">FTT</gloss> in Europe Recovery
                        Program.<note n="2" xml:id="d365fn2">For text, see Department of State
                        Treaties and Other International Acts Series (<gloss target="#t_TIAS1"
                            >TIAS</gloss>) No. 1845, or 62 Stat. (pt. 3) 3026.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent Department 679, repeated Paris 117.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Joyce</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
